text: Tomasgårdens IF was a floorball club at the Thomas Church in Västerås in Sweden, established as a club in 1982 following the 1978 establishment of a floorball team and disestablished in 1999 following the merger with Västerås IBF. The men's team won the Swedish national championship in 1984, and played in the Swedish top division during the 1990s, losing the 1991 Swedish national championship finals to IBK Lockerud. == References == Category:1999 disestablishments in Sweden Category:1982 establishments in Sweden Category:Sport in Västerås Category:Sports clubs disestablished in 1999 Category:Sports clubs established in 1982 Category:Swedish floorball teams
